---
export const prerender = true;
import BlogLayout from '../../layouts/BlogLayout.astro';
import '../../styles/global.css';
---

<BlogLayout
  title="Words Containing OE — Scrabble Word List & Strategy"
  description="Complete list of Scrabble words containing OE with scores, definitions, and strategic tips. Master OE words for better Scrabble plays."
  keywords="scrabble words containing oe, oe words scrabble, words with oe, scrabble oe word list, oe scrabble strategy"
>
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({
    "@context": "https://schema.org",
    "@type": "Article",
    "headline": "Words Containing OE — Scrabble Word List & Strategy",
    "description": "Complete list of Scrabble words containing OE with scores, definitions, and strategic tips.",
    "datePublished": "2026-06-15",
    "author": { "@type": "Organization", "name": "ScrabbleWordsFinder.com", "url": "https://www.scrabblewordsfinder.com" },
    "publisher": { "@type": "Organization", "name": "ScrabbleWordsFinder.com" },
    "mainEntityOfPage": { "@type": "WebPage", "@id": "https://www.scrabblewordsfinder.com/blog/words-containing-oe" }
  })} />

  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({
    "@context": "https://schema.org",
    "@type": "FAQPage",
    "mainEntity": [
      { "@type": "Question", "name": "What are the highest-scoring OE words in Scrabble?", "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "Top OE words include PHOENIX (19 pts), POEM (8 pts), POET (6 pts), DOES (5 pts), and SHOE (7 pts). OE is a niche pair appearing in about 150 valid Scrabble words." } },
      { "@type": "Question", "name": "How many Scrabble words contain OE?", "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "Around 150 valid Scrabble words contain OE. Common examples include POEM, POET, DOES, GOES, SHOE, CANOE, PHOENIX, and ALOE." } },
      { "@type": "Question", "name": "What strategy works best with OE tiles?", "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "OE is a niche pair with ~150 words. The -OE ending (SHOE, CANOE, ALOE, FLOE, TOE) is highly hookable with S. The -OES plural pattern (DOES, GOES, TOES, SHOES) provides easy extensions. PHOENIX (19 pts) is the premium OE target. OE also appears in POEM and POET for mid-game plays." } }
    ]
  })} />

  <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 py-12">
    <article class="prose prose-invert prose-gray max-w-none">
      <nav class="text-sm text-gray-400 mb-6 not-prose flex items-center gap-1">
        <a href="/blog/" class="hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">← Blog</a>
        <span class="mx-1">›</span>
        <span class="text-gray-300">Letter Pair Content</span>
      </nav>

      <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold text-white mb-4">Words Containing OE — Scrabble Word List & Strategy</h1>

      <div class="not-prose mb-8 flex items-center gap-3 text-sm text-gray-400">
        <time datetime="2026-06-15">June 15, 2026</time>
        <span class="w-1 h-1 rounded-full bg-gray-600"></span>
        <span>4 min read</span>
        <span class="w-1 h-1 rounded-full bg-gray-600"></span>
        <a href="/" class="inline-flex items-center gap-1 text-blue-400 hover:underline"><span aria-hidden="true">🔤</span> Word Finder</a>
      </div>

      <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed text-gray-300 mb-8">OE is a niche vowel pair appearing in about 150 valid Scrabble words. While the word count is smaller, OE features some gems — PHOENIX (19 pts) is a powerhouse, and the -OE ending (SHOE, CANOE, ALOE) provides highly hookable plays. Knowing OE words gives you an edge when opponents overlook this uncommon but valuable combination.</p>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Top OE Words by Score</h2>

      <div class="overflow-x-auto not-prose my-6">
        <table class="w-full text-sm border border-gray-700 rounded-lg overflow-hidden shadow-sm">
          <thead class="bg-gray-800">
            <tr>
              <th class="px-4 py-3 text-left font-semibold text-gray-300">#</th>
              <th class="px-4 py-3 text-left font-semibold text-gray-300">Word</th>
              <th class="px-4 py-3 text-left font-semibold text-gray-300">Points</th>
              <th class="px-4 py-3 text-left font-semibold text-gray-300">Definition</th>
            </tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody class="divide-y divide-gray-800">
            <tr class="bg-gray-900"><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">1</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-white font-medium">PHOENIX</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-blue-400">19</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">A mythical bird reborn</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-800/50"><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">2</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-white font-medium">POEM</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-blue-400">8</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">A literary verse</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-900"><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">3</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-white font-medium">SHOE</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-blue-400">7</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">Footwear</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-800/50"><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">4</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-white font-medium">CANOE</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-blue-400">7</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">A narrow boat</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-900"><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">5</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-white font-medium">POET</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-blue-400">6</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">One who writes verse</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-800/50"><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">6</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-white font-medium">DOES</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-blue-400">5</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">Performs an action</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-900"><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">7</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-white font-medium">GOES</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-blue-400">5</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">Moves or travels</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-800/50"><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">8</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-white font-medium">ALOE</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-blue-400">4</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">A succulent plant</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-900"><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">9</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-white font-medium">FLOE</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-blue-400">7</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">A sheet of ice</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-800/50"><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">10</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-white font-medium">TOE</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-blue-400">3</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">A foot digit</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-900"><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">11</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-white font-medium">FOE</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-blue-400">6</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">An enemy</td></tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </div>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10">
        <div class="flex flex-wrap items-center justify-center gap-6 text-center">
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">~150</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Valid OE words</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">7 pts</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Average score</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">Niche</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Pair frequency</p></div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Strategy Tips for OE Words</h2>

      <p>The -OE ending (SHOE, CANOE, ALOE, FLOE, TOE, FOE) is highly hookable — just add S. The -OES plural (DOES, GOES, TOES, SHOES, CANOES) gives easy parallel play extensions. PHOENIX (19 pts) is a spectacular target that uses both PH and X. POEM (8 pts) and POET (6 pts) are quick plays with common tiles. Remember FOE (6 pts) and FLOE (7 pts) as short defensive plays.</p>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 flex flex-wrap items-center justify-center gap-3">
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">PHOENIX</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">19 pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">POEM</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">8 pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">SHOE</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">7 pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">CANOE</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">7 pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">FLOE</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">7 pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">FOE</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">6 pts</span></span>
      </div>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-5 rounded-xl border border-blue-500/30 bg-blue-950/20">
        <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-blue-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-2">🎯 Key Takeaway</p>
        <p class="text-base text-gray-200">OE provides <span class="text-white font-medium">~150 valid words</span> — a niche but rewarding pair. PHOENIX (19 pts) is the crown jewel. SHOE (7 pts) and CANOE (7 pts) are reliable hookable plays. The -OE ending words take S easily, making them excellent for parallel play setups.</p>
      </div>

      <aside class="border-t border-gray-800 mt-12 pt-8 not-prose">
        <h3 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-4">Related Articles</h3>
        <div class="grid gap-3">
          <a href="/blog/words-containing-qu/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group"><span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span><span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Words Containing QU — Essential Scrabble Q Words</span></a>
          <a href="/blog/words-with-multiple-vowels/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group"><span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span><span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Words With Multiple Vowels — Scrabble Vowel Dumps</span></a>
          <a href="/blog/four-letter-words-every-player-should-know/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group"><span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span><span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Four-Letter Words Every Scrabble Player Should Know</span></a>
        </div>
      </aside>

      <div class="not-prose mt-10 p-5 bg-gradient-to-r from-blue-900/20 to-blue-800/20 border border-blue-800 rounded-xl">
        <div class="flex items-center justify-between gap-4 flex-wrap">
          <p class="text-sm text-blue-300 font-medium">🔤 Find every OE word from your tiles — instant results, no signup</p>
          <a href="/" class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 px-4 py-2 rounded-lg bg-blue-500 hover:bg-blue-400 text-gray-950 text-sm font-semibold transition-colors">Open Word Finder →</a>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="not-prose mt-8 text-center">
        <a href="/blog/" class="text-sm text-gray-400 hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">← Back to all articles</a>
      </div>
    </article>
  </div>
</BlogLayout>
